- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper introduces a new problem and studies its complexity. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper uses logical reasoning to prove complexity results. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper studies the complexity of the problem under different constraints. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the problem can be applied to scheduling and concurrent programming.
